
Fetch API:

The global fetch() method starts the process of fetching resources 

from the network, returning a promise which is fullfilled once the 

response is available.


fetch API- is one of the web API (its inbuild with javascript) 


example web API


DOM

HTML DOM


The fecth API Provides an interface for fetching resources

(including across the network).


it also provides a global fectch()



fetch("url",{method:'get' or 'post' or 'update' or 'delete'})

.then(response=>response.json())

.then(response=>console.log(response))

.catch(err=>console.log(err))





function myrequest(){


fetch( 'url',{ method:'get'});


.then(response=>response.json());


.then(response=>console.log(response));


.catch(err=>console.log(err));

}


fecthing single data from the array.


function username(){


fetch('url',{method:'get'})

.then(response=>response.json());

.then(response=>response.map(user=user.username));

.then(username=>console.log(username));

.catch(err=>console.log(err));

}





<html>

<head>

<title>document</head>

<script src="script.js"></script>

</head>

<body>

<h1>welcome to my webpage</h1>

<button onclick=myrequest()>request to server</button>

</body>

</html>





